<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-1-4-compound-units">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Jenna is studying in Finland this term and rented an older car to drive. Her car gets 7.6 kilometers per liter; she'd like to convert that to miles per gallon (mpg).
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use the fact that 1 mile <m>\approx</m> 1.609 km to write down two unit conversion fractions:
                    <me>
                        1 \approx \dfrac{<fillin fill="2.54" /> \text{ mile}}
                                        {<fillin fill="1.00" /> \text{ km}}
                        \quad \text{and} \quad
                        1 \approx \dfrac{<fillin fill="2.54" /> \text{ km}}
                                        {<fillin fill="1.00" /> \text{ mile}}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use the fact that 1 liter <m>\approx</m> 1.057 quarts to write down two unit conversion fractions:
                    <me>
                        1 \approx \dfrac{<fillin fill="2.54" /> \text{ liter}}
                                        {<fillin fill="1.00" /> \text{ quarts}}
                        \quad \text{and} \quad
                        1 \approx \dfrac{<fillin fill="2.54" /> \text{ quarts}}
                                        {<fillin fill="1.00" /> \text{ liter}}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use the fact that 1 gallon = 4 quarts,<aside><p>Incidentally, this is why they're called <q>quarts</q> -- they're a <q>quart</q>er of a gallon.</p></aside> together with your work from part (a) and part (b), to convert <m>\dfrac{7.6 \text{ km}}{1 \text{ liter}}</m> into miles per gallon.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>